  "description": [
    "THE VANCEDURG SUN Around The World With Circus v As I have been requested by friends aud relatives while at home visiting my parents Mr and Mrs B D Scott of Vance bnrg to giie a small account of my travels I have consented to try In 1908 I left Portsmouth Ohio for Columbus to join King ling Brothers big circus from tlier we went to Chattanooga Tenn where 1 remained nine months 1 Chattanooga Is a very beautiful place located at the base of Lookout Mountain and on the corner of Chickamauga Park 1 was very glad when we got our traveling orders to pro ceed to San Francisco and board a transport for the Phillipine Islands Had a pleasant tour crossing the continent and ar rived in San Francisco after a e days journey remaining thibre twelve hours and then took a transport for Honolulu Hawaii arriving there on the tenth day How if you will have patience for juBt a few minutes I will try and give you a little idea of the natives and their customs The city of Honolulu is about 80000 and about onethird of these are foreigners principally Ameri cans residing there for"
  ],
